.TH MU2EDAQ\-RESOURCE\-MANAGER 8 "2026-03-19" "1.0.0" "Mu2e DAQ"
.SH NAME
mu2edaq\-resource\-manager \- Mu2e DAQ hardware resource reservation server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B python3 server/app.py
.RB [ \-\-host
.IR HOST ]
.RB [ \-\-port
.IR PORT ]
.RB [ \-\-config
.IR FILE ]
.RB [ \-\-state
.IR FILE ]
.PP
.B scripts/start_server.sh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mu2edaq\-resource\-manager
is a FastAPI-based HTTP server that manages hardware resource reservations
for the Mu2e data acquisition system at Fermilab.
It tracks shared DAQ hardware (DTCs, CFOs, ROCs, EventBuilders) distributed
across multiple nodes and provides an atomic reserve/release API so that
multiple DAQ processes can coordinate exclusive access without conflicts.
.PP
Resources are defined statically in a YAML configuration file.
Reservation state is persisted to a JSON file and restored on restart,
so in-progress reservations survive server restarts.
.PP
All reservation operations are all-or-nothing: if any resource in a request
is unavailable or does not exist, the entire request is rejected and no
resources are modified.
.PP
A web UI is served at
.B /
when the
.I web/
directory is present.
Interactive API documentation (Swagger UI) is available at
.BR /docs .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-host " HOST"
IP address or hostname to bind.
Default:
.B 0.0.0.0
(all interfaces).
.TP
.BI \-\-port " PORT"
TCP port to listen on.
Default:
.BR 8080 .
.TP
.BI \-\-config " FILE"
Path to the YAML resource configuration file.
Default:
.IR config/resources.yaml .
Can also be set via the
.B RM_CONFIG
environment variable.
.TP
.BI \-\-state " FILE"
Path to the JSON state file used to persist reservation state across restarts.
Default:
.IR config/state.json .
Can also be set via the
.B RM_STATE
environment variable.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RM_HOST
Default bind host (overridden by
.BR \-\-host ).
.TP
.B RM_PORT
Default bind port (overridden by
.BR \-\-port ).
.TP
.B RM_CONFIG
Default config file path (overridden by
.BR \-\-config ).
.TP
.B RM_STATE
Default state file path (overridden by
.BR \-\-state ).
.SH API ENDPOINTS
.TP
.B GET /api/resources
List all resources.
Accepts an optional
.B ?status=available|reserved
query parameter.
.TP
.B GET /api/resources/{class}/{name}/{enum}
Get a specific resource by its three-part identifier.
Returns 404 if not found.
.TP
.B POST /api/reserve
Reserve one or more resources for a client.
Body: JSON object with
.B client_id
(string) and
.B resources
(array of
.BR {resource_class,\ name,\ enumerator} ).
Returns 409 if any resource is unavailable.
.TP
.B POST /api/release
Release one or more resources owned by a client.
Body: same structure as
.BR /api/reserve .
Returns 400 if a resource is not reserved or is owned by a different client.
.TP
.B DELETE /api/clients/{client_id}/resources
Release all resources currently held by
.IR client_id .
.TP
.B GET /api/status
Return a summary with total, available, and reserved resource counts.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I config/resources.yaml
Static hardware resource definitions.
Edit to add or remove resources; restart the server to apply changes.
.TP
.I config/state.json
Persistent reservation state.
Written atomically via a temporary file.
Do not edit by hand.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start with defaults:
.PP
.RS
.nf
./scripts/start_server.sh
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start on a specific interface and port:
.PP
.RS
.nf
python3 server/app.py --host 127.0.0.1 --port 9090
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start with a custom config:
.PP
.RS
.nf
RM_CONFIG=/etc/mu2edaq/resources.yaml ./scripts/start_server.sh
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rm\-cli (1),
.BR rm_cli.py (1),
.BR rm\-demo (1),
.BR demo_client.py (1)
